    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're saying one side of the debate just doesn't matter. if someone thinks the waste disposal or the potential for a meltdown is a dealbreaker regardless of the statistics, are they just \"clinging to fears\" or is that a valid ethical concern? why can't both views be treated as legitimate parts of the discussion?",
